snippet.title: Amber Heard and Johny Depp | Career Highlights of Heard
snippet.description:
Amber Heard and Johny Depp | Career Highlights of Heard.

Amber Heard acted in Aquaman, London Fields, Justice League, and others. She was married to Johnny Depp between 2015 and 2017. Amber Heard was born in Austin, Texas, in 1986. When she was 17, she dropped out of high school and moved to Los Angeles to pursue an acting and modeling career. Her first movie role was in the 2004 sports drama "friday night lights," which starred billy bob thornton. (It later became a TV show.). Amber Heard appeared in the Academy Award-nominated film, North Country (2005), in which she played Charlize Theron's character in flashbacks. Her major acting breakthrough came when she was cast as the title character, a shy outsider turned teen mass-murderer, in All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006). Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. HOLLYWOOD, June 7 (UPI) -- Amber Heard, who has accused husband Johnny Depp of domestic violence, was herself arrested on that charge in 2009 in an incident involving. Having starred opposite Nicolas Cage in the 2011 film Drive Angry and opposite her ex Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary and London Fields. Heard was told she was throwing away her. Heard filed for divorce against Depp on May 23, 2016 and four days later requested a temporary domestic violence restraining order against him, which a judge granted.
